Therefore, USD0 is not exposed to the fractional reserve of banks.USD0 is based on the regulated architecture of Hashnote structured in the form of a regulated MMF. Hashnote's assets are in custody at BNY ensuring to avoid any counterparty risk.

results.name: Ripple USD
results.description: Ripple USD is a USD denominated stablecoin created with trust, liquidity, and compliance at its core. Each RLUSD is backed by at least an equivalent amount of U.S. dollars and other cash equivalents. RLUSD is purpose-built for cross-border payments and delivers reliable access to digital dollars.
results.transparency_description: The Ripple USD stablecoin will have monthly attestations conducted by a third-party auditor. These reports will provide information on the amount of RLUSD minted and burned in the given month, the circulating supply of RLUSD, and details on the Ripple USD Reserve. Ripple will maintain a transparency webpage that will be updated regularly to provide the latest information on the circulating supply and the reserve.
results.holder_rights_description: Sending RLUSD to another blockchain address automatically transfers and assigns to that holder, and any subsequent holder, the right to redeem RLUSD for an equivalent amount of U.S. dollars from Ripple so long as the holder of such RLUSD is eligible to, and does, become a Customer.
results.fork_rights_description: Ripple retains the rights to fork at will.
results.peg_maintenance_description: The Ripple USD Reserve is kept in a combination of cash and cash equivalents. Each RLUSD token is backed 1:1 by the reserve. Reserve assets can be the following: cash, cash equivalents, and Short-term United States Treasury Bills.
results.legal_structure__description: New York, U.S. Limited Purpose Trust Company
results.regulatory_framework: New York State, U.S. Virtual Currency Business
results.governing_body: NYDFS - New York State Department of Financial Services
results.primary_market__subscription_description: Ripple, via SCTC, will perform mint and burn operations to manage the supply of the stablecoin. The stablecoin will be made available to Direct Customers (exchanges, market makers and other onboarded institutional customers). Indirect Customers (retail users) will be able to trade and acquire the stablecoin on exchanges and other Ripple Direct Customers, but they will not be able to obtain Ripple USD directly from Ripple.
results.accounts_segregated_description: SCTC maintains a reserve of high-quality, liquid assets (the “Reserve”) having an aggregate market value expressed in U.S. dollars, as of 5:00 pm New York time on each day the Federal Reserve Bank of New York is open (a “Business Day”), at least equal to the number of then outstanding RLUSD multiplied by one (1) U.S. dollar. The purpose of the Reserve is to provide U.S. dollars to satisfy RLUSD redemptions. Subject to Applicable Law, SCTC shall maintain the Reserve in accounts that are segregated from SCTC’s other assets, at depository institutions and securities custodians, as applicable, in one or more of the following asset classes: (a) U.S. Treasury bills three months or less from their respective maturities; (b) reverse repurchase agreements fully collateralized by U.S. Treasury bills, notes, and/or bonds on an overnight basis; (c) U.S. government money-market funds; and (d) deposit accounts.
results.holdings_bankruptcy_remote_description: Reserve assets will be placed in segregated structures and will not commingle such assets with its own funds.
results.deposit_insurance_description: (i) U.S. state or federally chartered depository institutions with deposits insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (“FDIC”) and/or (ii) asset custodians approved in advance in writing by NYDFS

results.name: Open Money USD
results.description: omUSD: the first digital cash backed by liquid, tokenized U.S. government debt. Unlike other RWA-backed stablecoins, Open Money is a DAO, free from centralized control or key individuals. It’s a truly decentralized, community-driven stablecoin, with 90% of governance tokens set to belong to the community.
results.primary_market__subscription_description: In order to mint omUSD token, minter should request mint by calling depositUSDC function of a FinanceHub smart contract (0xBD47522daFC402f64519de1FA86007A894fEe898). Minimum deposit is a parameter controlled by DAO, initially set to 1k USDC.  If at least one deposit is registered, all deposited tokens should be processed by calling requestSubscription function which can be called by any Ethereum user. This function, once called, forwards accumulated USDC to the OUSG protocol, and await for Ondo preccessing. After receiving approval from Ondo any user can execute claimOmUSD function and mint omUSD and distributes it to original depositors with 1:1 ratio to their USDC deposits.
results.primary_market__redemption_description: In order to burn omUSD token, burner should request redemption by calling depositOmUSD function of a FinanceHub smart contract (0xBD47522daFC402f64519de1FA86007A894fEe898). Minimum burn amount is a parameter controlled by DAO, initially set to 1k omUSD.  If at least one burning deposit is registered, any Ethereum user can call requestRedemptionDAO function which will send OUSG amount, equal to omUSD aggregated at the moment of redemption request, to OUSG protocol. After processing redemption request by Ondo the redemption process can be finalized by calling distributeUSDC function burn omUSD and receive USDC and distribute it to original burners with 1:1 ratio to their omUSD burns.
results.accounts_segregated_description: omUSD is 100% backed by the dollar value equivalent to the OUSG held by the protocol. The DAO cannot use the funds. omUSD only issued against the deposit of 1$ of OUSG.
